! Glycine conformer II / gly(2), MSR-compatible Cartesian rs input.
! Geometry: Cs DPCS3 geometry supplied by the user, reordered to the McGlone
! isotopologue atom numbering.
! B0 constants: McGlone et al., Table 11. Parent, 15N, 13C and selected
! deuterated species in Table 11 are taken there from Godfrey and Brown.
! dbvib: zero-point corrections Ae-A0, Be-B0, Ce-C0 from the Gly-IIp column
! of Table 9 supplied in the development notes. MSR dbvib is additive:
! corrected constants are Be = B0 + dbvib.
! The Cs model makes the two CH2 hydrogens and the two NH2 hydrogens equivalent
! by symmetry. Only the carbon-bound C-H distances are fixed to DPCS3 values.

